virtual machine (VM ):-
     a virtual machine is a software based computer running in cloud . 
a vm provides :- CPU, RAM , STORAGE , OPERATING SYSTEM  .
uses :- hosting websites 
        testing environments 
        running applications 
 
 {vm means clouds computer }

VIRTUAL MACHINE SCALE SETS (VMSS) :-
  vmss allows azure to automatically create and manage multiple  VM instances .
{automatically increase or decrease vm based on its demand }
benefits :- automatic scalling 
            high availability 
            load distribution 
    (vmss = automatic scalling of vm .)

    CONTAINERS :- 
     containers package an application with all its dependencies . 
     benefits :- fast startup 
                light weight 
                consistent environment
                same app works everywhere application + dependencies 

    e.g. popular container platform =  docker 

    AZURE FUNCTIONS :-  azure functions is a serverless computing service . you only write codes .
    azure manages :- servers 
                     scalling 
                     infrastructure 
        e.g. :- when a file is uploaded 
                file upload >>>>> azure function runs >>>>. send emails 

                difference between VM and container 
                vm                 vs                container 
                ________________________________________________
            heavier                 |       lightweight 
            full os included        |       shares host OS 
            slower startup          |       fast startup 
            more Resources          |       less resources 


AZURE APP SERVICE :- 
 azure app service is a fully managed platform for hosting web applications , APIs , and mobile beckends .
 benefits :- no server management 
            automatic scalling 
            built in security 
    {host websites without managing servers }

    AZURE CONTAINER INSTANCES  (ACI) :- 
    azure container instances allow you to run containers directly in azure without managing virtual machines .
in container = container >>>> vm >>>>> azure 
in ASI = container >>>>> azure 

AZURE networking ;- 
 
 virtual network (vnet ) :- a virtual network is a private network in azure that allows azure resources to communicate securely .
 as like home wifi , azure vnet . 
 vms , databases , apps , communicates under one Vnet . 

 SUBNET ::- a small network inside vnet .

 {vnet = large network 
 subnet = small network inside vnet } 

 NETWORK SECURITY GROUP (NSG) :- 
 NSG is used to control inbound and outbound network traffic .
